475
00:33:17,149 --> 00:33:20,102
Over there. Two pounds for
the eiderdown. Ladies and gentlemen.

476
00:33:20,222 --> 00:33:23,502
Mr Wix. We're having a meeting.

477
00:33:44,965 --> 00:33:48,126
Shut up.

478
00:33:48,237 --> 00:33:50,122
Me on the committee?

479
00:33:50,233 --> 00:33:52,434
I said they might want to elect you.
Who knows?

480
00:33:52,547 --> 00:33:55,271
Edie Randall, MP for Burgundy.

481
00:33:58,573 --> 00:34:00,774
They're all jelly!
All jelly! Jellied eels!

482
00:34:00,888 --> 00:34:02,969
Two bob and pick where you like!
Lovely lot of jellied eels!

483
00:34:03,082 --> 00:34:05,567
Jellied eels, they're champion!

484
00:34:05,677 --> 00:34:07,683
Thank you, sir.

485
00:34:07,792 --> 00:34:10,276
- Oi, manners, you!
- These ain't Danish eels.

486
00:34:10,386 --> 00:34:13,143
- What, do you think I'd cheat the public?
- I know an Irish eel when I see it.

487
00:34:13,259 --> 00:34:15,700
OK, have me arrested.

488
00:34:15,813 --> 00:34:18,853
All right, laugh while you can. We'll
soon have you twisters out of here.

489
00:34:18,966 --> 00:34:20,764
Yeah? What with? Your air force?

490
00:34:21,919 --> 00:34:24,436
Fancy! Start a new country
when they don't know how to protect it.

